\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 113. C. hispanica} Willk. in Willk. & Lange, {\i Prodr. Fl. Hisp.}{\b  2}: 291 (1868). Perennial. Rhizome usually stout, with few branches. Stems (15-)20-40(-75) cm, ascending to erect, hairy below. Basal leaves cordate, serrate, absent at anthesis; cauline narrowly lanceolate to linear, usually crowded in the lower part of stem, the lower serrate, the others entire. Inflorescence lax or contracted, rather few-flowered. Buds erect. Ovary papillose, rarely smooth. Calyx-teeth linear, appressed. Corolla (8-)10-14(-16) mm, infundibuliform. Capsule 5-7 mm, turbinate to conical, pendent, woody. {\i Rocks and stony or sandy places. • N., C. & E. Spain, just extending into France.} Ga Hs.
