\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 115. C. hercegovina} Degen & Fiala,{\i  Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  44}: 303 (1894). Perennial. Rhizome stout, woody, with few branches. Stems (8-)12-20(-40) cm, branched, ascending to pendent, angular, ciliate to hairy in the lower part. Basal leaves cordate to ovate, incise-serrate, absent at anthesis; cauline rhombic to ovate serrate to entire, petiolate. Inflorescence more or less branched. Buds erect. Ovary papillose. Calyx-teeth linear to setaceous. Corolla (14-)16-20(-22) mm. Capsule turbinate, pendent, woody. 2n = 34.{\i  Limestone rock-crevices. • S.W. Jugoslavia.} Ju.
